---
# Base clang-tidy configuration for all first-party code (src/ and examples/).
#
# This lives at the repository root rather than in src/ so that every first-party
# tree resolves to it by clang-tidy's normal parent-directory search, and so that
# tools invoked from the root (run-clang-tidy, IDEs) find a config at all instead
# of failing with "No checks enabled". Vendored third-party code under _deps/ is
# kept out of linting by CMake, which clears CMAKE_CXX_CLANG_TIDY across the
# dependency fetch -- see the top-level CMakeLists.txt.
#
# Module-local overrides live in src/<module>/.clang-tidy and use
# `InheritParentConfig: true` so they extend rather than replace this file.
#
# A bare `-some-check` with no rationale is indistinguishable from an accident,
# so record the reasoning here when disabling something. Note that YAML folded
# scalars cannot carry `#` comments, hence this block rather than inline notes.
#
# Deliberate, standing policy decisions:
#
#   * Unchecked container access. The whole `pro-bounds-*` family is off: this is
#     a terminal emulator whose hot paths index grid buffers by computed offset,
#     and bounds-checked accessors are neither free nor more correct here.
#     `pro-bounds-avoid-unchecked-container-access` (new in LLVM 20) is simply the
#     fourth member of that family and flagged 2470 sites.
#
#   * C-style casts. `cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-cstyle-cast` has long been off;
#     `modernize-avoid-c-style-cast` (new in LLVM 22) restates the same rule under
#     a different name and flagged 426 sites. Kept consistent with the former.
#
#   * Brace style. `readability-braces-around-statements` has long been off;
#     `readability-inconsistent-ifelse-braces` (new in LLVM 21) polices the same
#     area and flagged 179 sites. Brace style is settled by .clang-format.
#
#   * `modernize-use-designated-initializers` -- deliberate, see commit 8cd3d714.
#   * `portability-avoid-pragma-once` (394) -- `#pragma once` is the house include guard.
#   * `misc-include-cleaner` (4380) -- include hygiene is pursued separately, via
#     scripts/check-includes.sh and the self-contained-includes workflow.
#   * `misc-non-private-member-variables-in-classes` (1038) -- exact duplicate of
#     the cppcoreguidelines- check of the same name, which is already disabled.
#   * `bugprone-std-namespace-modification` (29) -- every report is a std::formatter
#     specialization for a program-defined type, which [namespace.std] explicitly
#     permits. The check does not distinguish that from adding new declarations.
#   * `misc-multiple-inheritance` (14) -- unavoidable and idiomatic here. Qt requires
#     QObject plus an interface for TerminalSession, TerminalSessionManager,
#     ContourGuiApp and TerminalAccessible, and crispy::overloaded is the standard
#     `struct overloaded: Ts...` visitor idiom the check cannot recognise.
#   * `cppcoreguidelines-use-enum-class` (3) -- vtbackend::Modifier, LockKey and
#     MatchModes::Flag are bitmask enums whose values are protocol-defined bit
#     positions, combined with bitwise operators throughout. Scoping them would
#     require a cast at every use for no gain in type safety.
#   * `misc-header-include-cycle` (2) -- Parser.h includes Parser-impl.h at its end,
#     the usual template-implementation split rather than a real cycle. The
#     Selector.h/ViInputHandler.h pair is a genuine mutual dependency and worth
#     untangling separately; it is not a lint fix.
#   * `clang-analyzer-optin.performance.Padding` (1) -- reordering vtbackend::Settings'
#     44 fields by size would save 32 bytes on a single long-lived object while
#     destroying the grouping that makes it readable.
#   * `bugprone-command-processor` (2) -- the two popen() calls are deliberate: shell
#     integration and process lookup both need a shell.
#   * `readability-function-size` (1) -- Screen::apply is the VT sequence dispatch
#     switch. Its size is the size of the protocol.
#   * `clang-analyzer-unix.BlockInCriticalSection` (1) -- it flags the ::read() that
#     UnixPty::read() performs under _mutex. The master fd is opened O_NONBLOCK
#     (UnixPty.cpp:228) and the read only runs once the selector has reported it
#     readable, so it cannot block; the checker classifies by function name rather
#     than by the descriptor's flags. Holding the lock across it is deliberate --
#     see 52d85da9, which added it to make read() safe against a concurrent close().
#   * `readability-qualified-auto` -- unsound for portable code. It rewrites `auto` to
#     `auto const* const` whenever the initializer's type is a pointer, and libstdc++
#     implements std::array's iterator AS a raw pointer -- so `std::ranges::find` over
#     a std::array satisfies it on Linux and fails to compile on MSVC, whose STL uses
#     a class type. Color.cpp already carried a comment warning about exactly this;
#     the check reverted that fix and broke the Windows build.
#   * `bugprone-chained-comparison` -- unavoidable with Catch2. CHECK(a == b) expands to
#     `Catch::Decomposer() <= a == b`, which is a chained comparison by construction,
#     so the check fires on ordinary assertions. Whether it does depends on how Catch2
#     is included, which is why a local sweep can measure zero and CI still fail.
#   * `misc-no-recursion` (41) -- recursion is a legitimate tool in a parser and a
#     renderer; the check flags the technique rather than any defect.
#   * `misc-use-anonymous-namespace` (79) -- directly contradicts
#     `misc-use-internal-linkage`, which is kept: that check gives functions and
#     variables internal linkage with `static` (its FixMode default) and reserves
#     anonymous namespaces for types, which cannot be `static`. Enabling both means
#     every symbol is flagged whichever form it takes.
#   * `readability-convert-member-functions-to-static` (100) -- its fix is malformed at
#     scale here: it emits `static` before `[[nodiscard]]`, where the attribute then
#     appertains to the return type rather than the function. It also makes Qt
#     Q_INVOKABLE methods static and strips their const, changing what QML binds to.
#   * `readability-redundant-member-init` (272) -- its fix is unsound here. Several
#     aggregates are built with designated initializers that omit fields, so a
#     `T member {};` default member initializer is load-bearing: dropping the `{}`
#     leaves the field uninitialized and trips -Wmissing-designated-field-initializers.
#
# The three LLVM 20/21/22 arrivals above were auto-enabled by the `cppcoreguidelines-*`,
# `modernize-*` and `readability-*` globs during the toolchain bump, silently
# contradicting policy this file already stated. Re-check this list when bumping LLVM.

Checks: >-
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  -bugprone-branch-clone,
  -bugprone-chained-comparison,
  -bugprone-command-processor,
  -bugprone-std-namespace-modification,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-exception-escape,
  -bugprone-reserved-identifier,
  -bugprone-suspicious-include,
  -bugprone-unchecked-optional-access,
  clang-analyzer-core.*,
  clang-analyzer-cplusplus.*,
  clang-analyzer-deadcode.*,
  clang-analyzer-nullability.*,
  clang-analyzer-optin.cplusplus.*,
  -clang-analyzer-optin.cplusplus.UninitializedObject,
  clang-analyzer-optin.performance.*,
  -clang-analyzer-optin.performance.Padding,
  clang-analyzer-optin.portability.*,
  clang-analyzer-security.*,
  clang-analyzer-unix.*,
  -clang-analyzer-unix.BlockInCriticalSection,
  clang-diagnostic-*,
  concurrency-*,
  cppcoreguidelines-*,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-c-arrays,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-const-or-ref-data-members,
  -cppcoreguidelines-use-enum-class,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers,
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-non-const-global-variables,
  -cppcoreguidelines-macro-usage,
  -cppcoreguidelines-no-malloc,
  -cppcoreguidelines-non-private-member-variables-in-classes,
  -cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-array-to-pointer-decay,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-avoid-unchecked-container-access,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-const-cast,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-cstyle-cast,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-static-cast-downcast,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-union-access,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg,
  -cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions,
  misc-*,
  -misc-include-cleaner,
  -misc-header-include-cycle,
  -misc-multiple-inheritance,
  -misc-no-recursion,
  -misc-use-anonymous-namespace,
  -misc-non-private-member-variables-in-classes,
  modernize-*,
  -modernize-avoid-bind,
  -modernize-avoid-c-arrays,
  -modernize-avoid-c-style-cast,
  -modernize-use-bool-literals,
  -modernize-use-designated-initializers,
  -modernize-use-scoped-lock,
  -modernize-use-trailing-return-type,
  performance-*,
  portability-*,
  -portability-avoid-pragma-once,
  -performance-no-int-to-ptr,
  readability-*,
  -readability-avoid-unconditional-preprocessor-if,
  -readability-braces-around-statements,
  -readability-convert-member-functions-to-static,
  -readability-else-after-return,
  -readability-function-size,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -readability-implicit-bool-conversion,
  -readability-inconsistent-ifelse-braces,
  -readability-magic-numbers,
  -readability-named-parameter,
  -readability-qualified-auto,
  -readability-redundant-access-specifiers,
  -readability-redundant-member-init,
  -readability-uppercase-literal-suffix,
  -readability-use-anyofallof,

# Every enabled check is a hard error. The codebase is clean under this list; see
# AGENT.md's zero-warning policy. Fix the cause rather than adding a NOLINT.
WarningsAsErrors: '*'

UseColor: true
HeaderFilterRegex: 'src/(contour|crispy|text_shaper|vtpty|vtparser|vtbackend|vtrasterizer|vtmux|vtconformance)/'
# Qt's AUTOMOC/AUTOUIC output lands under out/<preset>/src/<module>/..._autogen/, whose
# path matches HeaderFilterRegex; it is generated code and not ours to lint.
ExcludeHeaderFilterRegex: 'wayland-.*-protocol\.h|.*_autogen/.*|.*\.moc$'
FormatStyle: none

CheckOptions:
  cppcoreguidelines-explicit-virtual-functions.IgnoreDestructors: '1'
  modernize-loop-convert.MaxCopySize: '16'
  modernize-loop-convert.MinConfidence: reasonable
  modernize-loop-convert.NamingStyle: CamelCase
  modernize-pass-by-value.IncludeStyle: llvm
  modernize-replace-auto-ptr.IncludeStyle: llvm
  modernize-use-default-member-init.UseAssignment: '1'
  modernize-use-nullptr.NullMacros: 'NULL'
  # Pointer analysis proposes a const *pointee* where only the pointer itself could be
  # const, which is a different guarantee and breaks callers that write through it.
  misc-const-correctness.AnalyzePointers: 'false'
  readability-function-cognitive-complexity.Threshold: '50'
  readability-function-cognitive-complexity.IgnoreMacros: 'true'

  # Identifier naming. Types are CamelCase, everything else camelBack, with a
  # leading underscore on non-public data members. The snake_case modules
  # (crispy, text_shaper) override the type categories in their own configs.
  readability-identifier-naming.ClassCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.ClassConstantCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.ClassMemberCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.ClassMethodCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.ConstantCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.ConstantMemberCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.ConstantMemberPrefix: '_'
  readability-identifier-naming.ConstexprVariableCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.EnumCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.EnumConstantCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.ParameterCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.PrivateMemberCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.PrivateMemberPrefix: '_'
  readability-identifier-naming.PublicMemberCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.ScopedEnumConstantCase: CamelCase
  readability-identifier-naming.VariableCase: camelBack
  readability-identifier-naming.GlobalVariableCase: camelBack
  # No Hungarian notation: no g/s_/k prefixes. Globals are plain camelBack.
